'''Deej Warrick''' was an adventurous [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] warrior.

==Biography==
Deej and his wife, [[Shodu Warrick|Shodu]], had four children: [[Weechee Warrick|Weechee]], [[Widdle Warrick/Legends|Widdle]], [[Wicket Wystri Warrick/Legends|Wicket]] and [[Winda Warrick|Winda]]. Deej's paternal grandfather was [[Erpham Warrick]], the Ewok who made the famed [[Ewok battle wagon]].

One day, when Deej had taken his sons fishing, he cut himself on some sharp [[rokna tree fungus]], which caused him to fall deathly ill. He was nursed back to health by his loving wife, Shodu, while his children helped to find the ingredients for [[Logray/Legends|Logray]] to create an antidote to cure him. He recovered completely.

[[File:DeejWarrick-Ewoks.jpg|thumb|left|180px|Deej Warrick]]

While looking for his older sons one day, Deej spotted the [[Towani family]]'s [[Towani family star cruiser|fallen starcruiser]], and later helped [[Mace Towani|Mace]] and [[Cindel Towani]] find their parents.

==Behind the scenes==
Deej was performed by [[Daniel Frishman]] and voiced by [[Sydney Walker]] in both Ewok films.

